HEADWORD: Live-forever
<hw>Live"-for*ev`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A plant (<spn>Sedum Telephium</spn>) with fleshy leaves, which has
extreme powers of resisting drought; garden ox-pine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

